<noinclude>{{month|September}}
Events that occurred on 19 September.
==On Earth==
</noinclude>
* '''[[1916]]''' - Writer [[Terence Tiller]] is born.
* '''[[1931]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]], [[C.S. Lewis]] and [[Hugo Dyson]] have dinner, followed by a conversation that ran until 4 a.m. [[20 September|the following morning]] that was essential for Lewis's conversion to [[Christianity]].
* '''[[1943]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 49e]].
* '''[[1944]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter 80a]].
* '''[[1956]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter to Terence Tiller (19 September 1956)|a letter to Terence Tiller]].
* '''[[1962]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[Letter to Alina Dadlez (19 September 1962)|a letter to Alina Dadlez]].
* '''[[1965]]''' - [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] writes [[letter 277a]].
* '''[[1982]]''' - The article "[[The Sunday Times Magazine 19 September 1982|The Return of Tolkien]]" is published in ''The Sunday Times Magazine''.
* '''[[1986]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 1986]] at [[wikipedia:Oxford Town Hall|Oxford Town Hall]].
* '''[[1993]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 1993]] at [[wikipedia:University College, Oxford|University College]].
* '''[[1997]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 1997]] at [[wikipedia:Exeter College, Oxford|Exeter College]].
* '''[[2003]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 2003]] at [[wikipedia:St Hugh's College, Oxford|St Hugh's College]].
* '''[[2004]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 2004]] at [[wikipedia:St Hilda's College, Oxford|St Hilda's College]].
* '''[[2004]]''' - [[The Lord of the Rings Symphony]] at Mortensen Hall in [[wikipedia:Hartford, Connecticut|Hartford]], [[wikipedia:Connecticut|Connecticut]].
* '''[[2020]]''' - [[Oxonmoot 2020]] held online due to the [[wikipedia:COVID-19 pandemic|Covid-19 pandemic]].
